        <h3>Date/Time Format</h3>
        <p>
          Data imported into HTM Studio must be in CSV file format and meet the
          following conditions:
        </p>
        <ul class="fa-ul">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <li>
                <i class="fa fa-li fa-caret-right"></i>
                Only one Date/Time column
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fa fa-li fa-caret-right"></i>
                Only one header row
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fa fa-li fa-caret-right"></i>
                Number of rows in the CSV file should be minimum of 400.
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fa fa-li fa-caret-right"></i>
                Values in numeric columns will be skipped if equal to "NaN",
                "None", "null", "N/A", "NA" (not case sensitive)
              </li>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <li>
                <i class="fa fa-li fa-caret-right"></i>
                Any number of numeric columns
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fa fa-li fa-caret-right"></i>
                Data is listed in chronological order
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fa fa-li fa-caret-right"></i>
                Date/Time column must be in a
                <a href="{{site.paths.pages.htmstudio}}date-time-formats.html">
                  supported format
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fa fa-li fa-caret-right"></i>
                Unix timestamp support (both milliseconds and seconds) as long
                as the column name contains the words "time" or "date" (case
                insensitive)
              </li>
            </div>
          </div>
        </ul>
